  "description": {
    "en": {
      "provenance": "imported",
      "value": "Sustainable, Inclusive and Resilient WASH project in Nepal shall address the critical issue of WASH by adhering to meet SDG 6 vision paved by the 15th periodic plan and related government priorities. The project aims for equitable and sustainable improved drinking water, sanitation and good hygiene practices among marginalized and vulnerable families, communities and geography of Nepal. It shall be implemented in different municipalities of Bardiya, Siraha, Lalitpur, Kavrepalanchowk through local and technical counterparts in collaboration and coordination with federal, provincial and local governments and other key stakeholders."
    },
